<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870406-0174 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Roman Named ChairmanOf Ogilvy Group Ad Unit</HL><DD> 04/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS OGIL </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ogilvy Group Inc., the parent of several large advertising agencies, named Kenneth Roman as chairman of its Ogilvy andamp; Mather Worldwide unit and also named two new directors.    Mr. Roman was president of Ogilvy andamp; Mather Worldwide, the company's largest ad agency unit, which includes the Scali, McCabe, Sloves group, several independent agencies and marketing information services. Mr. Roman, who will retain his post as president, succeeds William E. Phillips, who remains chairman of the parent.    The company named to its board Ian Hunt, chairman and chief executive officer of Research International, which the company acquired in January, and Hugh Parker, who serves on several boards and was managing director of the British unit of McKinsey andamp; Co., a management-consultant firm, until he retired in 1983. </TEXT></DOC>